Focus 15 is one of my favorites, RJ.  My only complaint is this:  I
like to listen to the areas where there is no talking louder than what
is comfortable where there is talking.  So, I normally turn the volume
up after the intro, get deeply into the CD, then I get startled when
the talking begins again!  :shock:

I have the Monroe single CD called The Visit, which is a nice guided
visualization to a cave where you can visit with those on the other
side.  The first time I used it, I met my grandmother and thought it
was a wonderful experience.

Gosh, they have so many titles to choose from!

Margaret

